                  Records Management Services
                  For State Agencies and Local Governments

   The New York State Archives and Records Administration provides records
   and information management services to State agencies and local
   governments in New York State. This page provides access to these
   services, which include publications, records management training, and
   direct assistance.

   For more information contact your Regional Advisory Officer or send an
   e-mail message to: recmgmt@mail.nysed.gov.
     * Local Government Records Management Improvement Fund (LGRMIF)
       Grants -- Provide support for records management and
       archives-related projects in local governments of all types and
       sizes throughout New York State.

     * Guidelines for Needs Assessments and Feasibility Studies for LGRMIF
       Grants (Also available to download in pdf format.)

     * Guidelines for Stand Alone Digital Imaging Systems

     * Producing High Quality Microfilm

     * Current Workshop Catalog

     * Records Management Publications for State Agencies and Local
       Governments

     * Records Retention and Disposition Schedules

     * Services for Managing Records Communicated via Electronic Mail

     * Records Management Software Guidelines

     * eGovernment -- an introduction to eGovernment (its history, its
       challenges, its benefits and its potential), paying special
       attention to the records management issues involved in setting up
       eGovernment services.

     * List of Other Records Management Services for State Agencies

     * List of Other Records Management Services for Local Governments
